This module selects the bank of audio for the current page. A new bank needs to be chosen at the start of each page, but because some outputs of the SELECT are ganged together then each bank will be selected more than once (facilitating a repeat). This allows more than one music track to be used for each process. The filenames are sent to 'Random Number Generator and Audio File Assignment' where the stimuli are randomly assigned to each scale.

This module returns the audio for each slider. The audio is replayed from a separate patcher: slideraudio. Double-click the slideraudio object to open the patcher.

The numbers above choose a column in this matrixctrl to turn on. The matrixctrl ensure only 1 option is selected per row. It outputs all changes as [column row value], where value is 0 for off and 1 for on. The row can be ignored. These values can be sent directly to the audio faders to open or close them. With some processing the value can be sent to "Scale Score Locking" in order to  control the gates that either pass the slider value or short-circuit it. Lastly, the buttons must also be set, which is again done directly using the value parameter.
This module selects the stimulus: changes the audio faders, the buttons, and locks/unlocks the appropriate sliders.
Main DAC module for patch receiving left and right signals from all sfplay functions. Receives play and stop commands from the Play Control module

This module controls the playback of the patch. Instructions are received from the play/pause button. Pressing the space bar or pressing "Play/Pause" will start or pause the audio. Pressing "Stop" or s will stop the audio. The Sync bang is sent to each channel to synchronise the audio and restart it from the beginning. The audio is stopped and re-synced at the end of each page

This module sets the search path of the patch as the folder (and all subfolders) in which the patch is contained. This path is also used by the automatic backup feature and is hence the location in which automatic backups are stored.
Random Number Generator and Audio File Assignment
This module packs the scores with the corresponding file names. The results are then written to a csv file - this happens automatically every page and is presented at the end of the test.

This module generates the random number sequence for each page. "urn" generates the pseudo-random numbers serially and "cycle" assigns them to each of their scales. Uzi fires the required number of bangs so that all random number slots (scales) are filled.
Loadbangs and zeros are transmitted throughout the patch to ensure the patch is ready for the next user
This section of the module automatically saves a time-stamped backup of the data after each page is completed
This module controls the pages, i.e. the displayed page number.
This module controls the reset of the page after it is reset. It also clears 'Text' in 'Export Results' at the end of the 6th page

This module validates the page before the user is allowed to continue. When the scale is moved, one bang is sent by onebang for each scale and the counter counts the number of bangs. Once the number of bangs reaches the number of scales the active status of the next button is changed and the user is allowed to use it.
The validation must be initialised after the scales have been reset, otherwise the onebangs will be triggered too early and the count will be complete before any scales are used.
